Target: OntoGreenspace is an ontology developed for representing greenspaces.

Comment: A spatial area object that is partly or completely covered with grass, trees, shrubs, or other vegetation
Label: Greenspace

Comment: A designated entry location that provides public or restricted access into a greenspace area
Label: Access Point

Comment: An identifier indicating the sequential appearance of a greenspace or access point within a single dataset
Label: has GID

Comment: A unique identifier that distinctly identifies a greenspace or access point across all datasets
Label: has ID

Comment: A description of the intended purpose of a greenspace
Label: has Function

Comment: The first alternative name for a greespace
Label: has First Alternative Name

Comment: The second alternative name for a greespace
Label: has Second Alternative Name

Comment: The third alternative name for a greespace
Label: has Third Alternative Name

Comment: The spatial geometry of a greenspace, detailing its shape and boundaries
Label: has Geometry

Comment: The type or level of access allowed at an access point, such as pedestrian, and motor vehicle and pedestrian
Label: has Access Type

Comment: The relationship linking the access point to its associated greenspace site
Label: has Reference To Greenspace Site
